<div id="review_341930967" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/341930967" />
    <a title="WTF Are You Reading?" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3603515-wtf-are-you-reading"><img alt="WTF Are You Reading?" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1476934869p2/3603515.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/341930967?book_show_action=true">Jun 03, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="WTF Are You Reading?" class="user" itemprop="url" name="WTF Are You Reading?" href="/user/show/3603515-wtf-are-you-reading">WTF Are You Reading?</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781463790738" href="/book/show/12436910-scorpio-rising">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer341930967" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12447111946402759276">Monique Domovitch has clearly shown herself to be a shining star within the genre of Romance. This captivating read provides it&apos;s audience a front row seat from which to witness the drama that seems to permeate the lives of both Alex Ivanov and Brigitte Dartois.<br/>Though each tale presents a separate story told from both a different vantage point as well as from opposite sides of the globe; the haunting shades of despair and desperation coupled with fiery hues of passion, hope, and determination pa</span>
  <span id="freeText12447111946402759276" style="display:none">Monique Domovitch has clearly shown herself to be a shining star within the genre of Romance. This captivating read provides it's audience a front row seat from which to witness the drama that seems to permeate the lives of both Alex Ivanov and Brigitte Dartois.<br />Though each tale presents a separate story told from both a different vantage point as well as from opposite sides of the globe; the haunting shades of despair and desperation coupled with fiery hues of passion, hope, and determination paint a picture of lives that the mind's eye must see to believe.<br />The seemingly endless reserves of emotionality found in this work, coupled with the complexity of an ever evolving plot, is reminiscent of masterpieces penned by long-standing greats such as Danielle Steele and Sidney Sheldon.<br /> It is hard to believe that this is Ms. Domovitch's first novel. I am happy to confidently predict that with talent such as this, it is far from her last.<br />You can see this review as it appears on my blog here: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.wtfareyoureading.com/2012/06/adult-romance-review-you-are-sure-to.html">http://www.wtfareyoureading.com/2012/...</a><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12447111946402759276" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


